<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Admiration for Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam</h1>
        <p>Remembering the Missile Man of India</p>
    </header>

    <main>
        <img src="kalam.jpg" alt="Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam">
        
        <p>
            Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam BR was an Indian aerospace scientist and statesman who served as the 11th president of India from 2002 to 2007. He was born and raised in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu and studied physics and aerospace engineering..Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam, the 11th President of India, was not only a visionary scientist but also an inspirational leader. His life and work continue to inspire millions around the world.
        </p>

        <p>
            Known as the "People's President," Dr. Kalam played a crucial role in India's civilian space program and military missile development. His dedication to education and his ability to connect with people, especially the youth, set him apart as a true leader.
        </p>

        <p>
            Dr. Kalam's humility, simplicity, and his emphasis on hard work and perseverance make him an enduring figure of admiration. His famous saying, "Dream, dream, dream. Dreams transform into thoughts, and thoughts result in action," encourages everyone to strive for their goals.
        </p>
    </main>

</body>
